Package CAMs_App.boundary

Class StaffCampMenu

java.lang.Object
CAMs_App.boundary.StaffCampMenu
All Implemented Interfaces:
Menu
public class StaffCampMenu extends Object implements Menu
The StaffCampMenu implements the generic menu, Menu. It provides methods to print the main menu and viewing the application. The class uses StaffController to manage staff-related activities and also uses CampManagementService in generating reports.

  • Method Details

    • printMenu

      public void printMenu()
      The printMenu() method displays the camp menu options available for staff user. It prints camp menu options for staff user such as edit camp, delete camp, toggle camp visibility, view enquiries, reply enquiries, view suggestions, process suggestions, approve suggestions, generate report, returning to previous page and logout.
      Specified by:
      printMenu in interface Menu

    • viewApp

      public void viewApp()
      The viewApp() method allows Staff user to perform various camp-related actions for the current camp such as

      • Edit camp : Staff user edits the current camp infomation through StaffController.editCamp().
      • Delete camp : Staff user deletes the current camp through StaffController.deleteCamp().
      • Toggle camp's visibility : Staff user toggles the current camp visibility through StaffController.toggleVisibility().
      • View enquiries for this camp : Staff user views the current camp's enquiries through StaffController.viewEnquiries().
      • Reply enquiries for this camp : Staff user replies the current camp's enquiries through StaffController.replyEnquiries().
      • View suggestions for this camp : Staff user views the current camp's suggestions through StaffController.viewSuggestions().
      • Process suggestions for this camp : Staff user processes the current camp's suggestions through StaffController.processSuggestions().
      • Approves suggestions for this camp : Staff user approves the current camp's suggestsions through StaffController.approveSuggestion().
      • Generate report : Staff user can either generate StaffController.generateCommitteeReport(), StaffController.generateStudentReport() orStaffController.generateEnquiriesReport(). These reports can be filtered to faculty or default (print all) by user input.
      • Go to previous page : Returns the Staff user back to StaffMenu.
      • Logout : Staff user logs out from the system and returning to the MainMenu.

      Invalid inputs prompts the user to choose again.

      Specified by:
      viewApp in interface Menu
